reviews_data.review_text: Absolutely love the atmosphere & staff. Love the mission & vision.
The peach rib and New Orleans chicken sandwich were so good.

While in the Charlotte area, I looked up places to eat breakfast and I came across this restaurant since it had pretty good reviews. When first coming in honestly  I didn't feel welcomed from the young lady at the desk. She just asked where would I like to sit at. She didn't specify or tell me that one side is like self serve and the other side you will have a server/waiter, that would have been nice to know especially since it was my first time but I learned that information from asking another staff member at the coffee side once I realized which side I chose,  while waiting to be waited on since I wasn't given a menu or anything. While sitting and watching I did notice how some others that came in were greeted by the same young lady at the door which is why I couldn't give 5 stars. However, to the good part. I'll upload a picture of what I ordered but I can honestly say these were the best cheese grits I ever tasted so far, I could eat it by itself! My food was a 4 1/2 and thats only because the potatoes tasted funny (sorry I can't explain this better) other than that my tea was good, and the rest of my food was good. I just wished the service, feeling more welcomed, just some type of advice/explanation kinda just something for someone that is new to the restaurant which I was sure to mention for that reason  when coming in. So, hopefully that is better next time because I have to go back again for those grits. Hopefully, I can edit this review and/or update with a better experience.

Food is good
Atmosphere good
Service needs improvement
The desserts are outstanding. The cause is even better. Love this place and the people.

What a lovely experience! The hospitable staff are kind and efficient. The food is well-presented and delicious. I was so moved by learning the testimony of this organization and the people it employs. What a blessing! Thanks!!!

Highly recommend! Delicious food in a bright and welcoming atmosphere. The whole staff were so friendly and polite! We brought our small baby and they were very kind and accommodating. The steak and eggs was the best I've ever eaten. We no longer live in Charlotte otherwise I would eat here all the time.
I haven’t done the sit-down experience, but I love the cafe! I enjoyed everything and the staff is wonderful. My only complaint is that they aren’t open on weekends!

Delicious! The two-egg breakfast came with impressive chosen sides - really fresh fruit and tasty yogurt! Everything tasted high-quality and thoughtfully prepared. The setting is beautiful, with a warm and inviting atmosphere.
The food was delicious and whoever made my hazelnut expresso!? *MWAH* Chef’s Kiss!!!

The food, coffee, and people here are incredible! I met Will and his team and was blown away! Chef Shay and her crew made the most delicious food ever ! Sarah and Megan made sure everything was great for our shoot as well!

Community Matters is such a special piece of Charlotte. Their heart warming and inspiring mission brings customers through the door, but it’s the incredible food, fresh pastries, great drinks, and super friendly service that keeps us coming back. Be sure to try the BLT and Brussels — it’s next level :) thank you community matters for consistently being as phenomenal as you are, Charlotte cherishes you!

If want to dine at a restaurant in Charlotte where your money goes to a great cause go to Community Matters Cafe! This is the restaurant for Charlotte Rescue Mission where they give back to the community and provide a second chance for men & women to be productive in society. God doesn't give up on us when we go off track in life and this place doesn't give up on individuals. With a mission like this I go here once a week for breakfast!

Community Matters Cafe has a new menu for every season of the year. I highly recommend getting the Classic Cafe Breakfast with the sides being bacon & Brussel Sprouts! Also the egg sandwich is great as well! The new seasonal item i had for breakfast is the Pulled Pork Johnny Cakes which tasted great! B

Service was friendly and they have great staff as well who will take care of you!

reviews_data.review_text:
Wow! I did not have a good experience at this place. I am a remote worker, wanted to get some coffee and breakfast while checking some emails before taking some meetings at home later, and this place was highly recommended. As soon as we walked in, the environment was already a bit unwelcoming and the barista taking our order was short with us. Once we got the coffee we ordered, the extra hot drink didn't have a sleeve on it so we had to ask for one because it was too hot to hold.
We decided (against our better judgement) to go ahead with our plan to order food so we were seated, and sat for a long while before being able to put an order in — seems like the waitress may have forgotten we were there or not have noticed. My partner had just travelled a couple hours really early in the morning and so went to the bathroom to change their shoes and pants, and a waitress followed them and checked on them, maybe thinking they were doing something suspicious?
Once the food came, we were surprised to see the focaccia de jour had pork on it, and unfortunately my partner doesn't eat pork (our bad, we should have asked, but we also weren't told anything about what it came with, and the menu only said olive oil — which it didn't seem to have either). We waited ages for a server to come to our table so we could ask for something to replace it, like regular toast, and then another few ages for that to get to us. At the point that it did, it was nearing the time I needed to leave, and my partner was feeling extremely uncomfortable and anxious and so I went ahead to the host's stand to ask for to go boxes and to go ahead and close the check — it probably would have taken another 20 minutes to wait for someone to come to our table again.
If you're visibly queer or dress alternatively, I don't recommend coming here. I don't usually have any issues with either of these things in Charlotte, but the entire time we felt so incredibly judged and got constant stares from not only all of the staff but also the other customers. Service was not great, slow, and not very attentive. Did not come to check on us except to give us the check. I do appreciate that they removed the focaccia from our bill since my partner was not able to eat it. My partner did enjoy the french toast I ordered, but I was overall disappointed by the food and did not really like it much. The one positive interaction I had was with the host, who was very attentive, helped me get the boxes, and greeted me with a kind smile and was polite. Everyone else in the entire cafe made us feel very uncomfortable and unwelcome.
I do think the mission of the cafe is lovely and it seems like they have provided some great experiences for many customers, but unfortunately our visit was disappointing.
This place is absolutely amazing. The staff and the guests are so welcoming and friendly.
Pretty big breakfast spot. Wasn’t super busy at 7am. Friendly staff. Simple but yummy food. Decent coffee. Big parking lot. Community focused.

reviews_data.review_text:
My wife and I had a great breakfast here. I had the crème brûlée French toast 😋. Definitely recommend. It would be a great dish to share. It was sweet.

Overall the food, atmosphere, and staff were great! The best thing about this place is the help it provides to the recovering community is amazing. I wish I wasn’t terrible with names because our waitress was so awesome. She was very attentive and friendly we didn’t want for anything. Since it was our first time in she shared a little about her recovery and how this place helps with an easier transition back into the workforce.
A Cafe with a cause. This spot is great for meet ups and small gatherings. The service was great. Although they have a good coffee selection, they also have an equal selection of tea.

From the moment we walked in, we were greeted with warm smiles and a welcoming atmosphere at Community Matters Cafe. The environment is beautiful and peaceful, and you can feel the love and compassion throughout the space.

What truly made our experience exceptional was how the staff handled my son’s food allergy. The chef personally came to our table to speak with us and ensure his meal was safe—something that meant the world to us as parents. The level of care and attentiveness was above and beyond.

The food was absolutely top-notch—fresh, flavorful, and made with heart. Their mission and what they stand for is inspiring, and it shines through in everything they do.

We left with full bellies, big smiles, and some coffee to go! We can’t wait to come back and support this amazing place again.

I visited for the first time one week ago and the experience was amazing! I enjoyed the clean, cozy and welcoming atmosphere. Great for engaging friends or bring your laptop and work while sipping a finely crafted tea or nibbling on freshly prepared pastry. The menu is well rounded and delicious. I personally enjoyed the duck wings and Brussels sprouts. The staff and service was excellent and I love the mission and cause. I will definitely return.
Great staff, Great service, creative food with alot of flavor, all while giving back to the community! 👏 Amazing !!! I suggest highly!
Really greatfull! 👍 one of the best breakfast spot with great service.
Great coffee shop atmosphere and solid group lunch spot
The soup here was DIVINE today!!! Goodness to the soul! Who knew sunflower root could be used to make a delicious soup?! Sunchoke and mushroom cream soup - ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

Had a great lunch! The collard greens and cornbread were some of the best we have had. Salad was fresh, grilled chicken was moist, tumeric dressing was unique and tasty. Will definitely be back again!

What a fantastic place! I have been following Community Matters Cafe story and finally had a chance to try it out! It was all I had hoped it would be and more! As someone who has been deeply affected by substance abuse, I love the mission of community and dignity. And...the food and coffee - my goodness! The single best BLT I've ever had...I didn't know that toast could melt in your mouth! CMC has earned a loyal customer after one visit. Great job!

Corey was the sweetest server!
Enjoyed the SALTED HONEY CORTADO! Man that was the best coffee and I loved the grits! All around great place to meet friends or work remotely for a bit! Thank you!
The food was delicious, the atmosphere was great, and it was nice. That parking was really easy to find as well. I will definitely be coming back.

Soon as I walked in I was greeted and seated 🪑, nice environment I mean the scenery was relaxed and welcoming. Now, the food was a little bland, I ordered the “Cajun Sausage Skillet” and was highly disappointed 😔, that dish should be changed to “ Home Fry Skillet”. It was literally around 5 thinly sliced sausage and the rest of the skillet was filled with home fries. It looked a little suspicious 🤨 with the egg covering the skillet as if trying to hide the fact they ran out of sausage or something I’m not sure 🤷🏾‍♂️. My advice, take the egg off and make sure you get sausage if you decide to get this dish. A little over priced for such simple meals.

I would personally love to visit your place, but your current hours during the week don’t quite work for me, especially with the early closing times. Have you considered opening on weekends? That would be really beneficial for those of us who’d love to enjoy your food and coffee but only have weekends available.
Had  the Brussel sprouts, which I love the most and a nice hot tea. I would definitely bring my family and friends.

reviews_data.review_text: Waited too long for our drinks. I understand it can be busy but over 5 minutes and plenty off staff is a bit much for two simple espresso drinks. On top of that the cappuccino had a weird aftertaste like skim milk.

This was my first time, I was excited about the concept of a co working restaurant space. I ordered a beverage from their menu, and asked about an ingredient on a menu item for breakfast. Out of the two people taking orders, and the manager and other workers behind the counter, no one knew what about the menu item, so I passed on the food. After I ordered the drink, A 5th person ended up knowing about the menu and informed me of what it was.

So I ordered a beverage, with one modification. I waited at the counter for about five minutes For my drink (no line) And then was asked what I was waiting for. I let them know my drink order had not yet arrived so I was still waiting on that. They had lost the drink ticket, which is fine, completely understand. I let them know what I would like again and wait a couple more minutes. Then another someone to come up and tell me they cannot make the drink on ice (as I had ordered it) because they don’t have the capability to make the iced drink that I ordered. Mind you, they offer iced and frozen beverages.

After about 20 minutes, I get my drink and they did not include the modification (adding a syrup). I go back up to the coffee bar and ask to confirm that they put vanilla and lavender in the beverage as I had ordered, and was told nope only the lavender was in there. I stood there Foolishly, expecting them to offer to at least put the correct syrup in the drink, since I was informed 10 minutes after I ordered it, but they could not make the drink that I ordered. No offer to try and make anything right. I packed up my stuff and left, I will not be coming back.

I can look past not knowing your menu, I can look past losing my order, I can look past you telling me you can’t make the drink that I already paid for 10 minutes after I have been waiting, but after all that and it’s not even the flavor I ordered? Very disappointed.

I left disappointed. They were out of a menu item, the food took a long time to come out, and once it did, we weren't impressed with the quality and it was a little cold. Our server didn't really visit the table and it took another server noticing coffee was empty to get attention.

What a beautiful spot with an incredible mission. Interior is very cozy, with plenty of varied seating and places to sit and work or socialize. I had the spiced chai latte, and it's delicious. Staff is friendly and awesome.
Great place definitely will be going back to have a sit down
I loved going to the Community Matters Cafe. The food was to die for and I plan on going back. All my friends had great things to say.
Great lunch selection.  My chicken wrap was terrific

I can’t really comment on the food since we never received anything. We got there at 12:31pm. It wasn’t busy and 45 min later we were asked how we wanted to split the check. We told them we hadn’t received our food yet and they told us it was ‘on the fly’ 20 min later, they said it would be another 8 min. We left at 1:40pm without any food in sight.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Dear Michelle,
Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback. We are truly sorry to hear about your experience, as we strive to provide the best service possible. Your concerns are important to us, and we would love the opportunity to make things right.

Could you please reach out to us at the Cafe by calling 980-237-2147 and asking for Will Whitlow? We would appreciate the chance to discuss this further and ensure we address any issues you faced.

Thank you again for your feedback, and we hope to hear from you soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Good food, good coffees. Just wish they were open on weekends.
The aroma of coffee made me want some when I came in. We were warmly greeted and shown to an open table. The service and food were both great. We will have to return. Picture of my Johnny Cake dish.
Food was good. Six of us had 5 different menu items. Flapjacks and egg plates. French toast was not my fav but one kid liked it.

I recently had the most incredible birthday breakfast at this amazing spot! From the moment I walked in, the staff were welcoming. Their warm and friendly service truly set the tone for a memorable morning.

The food at this place is absolutely delicious. I ordered a coffee and their Rye sandwich, and it exceeded all expectations. The flavors were perfectly balanced, and the presentation was top-notch. Each bite was a delightful.

What made my birthday breakfast even more special was when the staff surprised me with a birthday cookie! It was such a thoughtful gesture that made me feel extra loved and appreciated. The cookie itself was scrumptious, with a soft center and just the right amount of sweetness.

The ambiance of this breakfast spot is cozy and inviting. It's the kind of place where you can relax, enjoy your meal, and soak in the positive energy. The decor is charming, and the atmosphere is buzzing with positivity.

I can't praise the staff enough for their exceptional service. They were attentive, friendly, and went above and beyond to make my birthday breakfast unforgettable. Their genuine care and attention to detail truly made me feel special. A special shout-out to Adriana!

I highly recommend this breakfast spot to anyone looking for a memorable dining experience. Whether it's a special occasion or just a regular morning, you'll be treated to amazing food, outstanding service, and a warm, welcoming atmosphere. I can't wait to go back and create more wonderful memories!

Thank you to the staff for making my birthday morning so incredibly special. You guys rock!
Lovely first time experience!! Plan to return 😊
Excellent food however you need to make a reservation if you intend to eat there. They have a place to mingle and drink coffee and beverages. Nice atmosphere.

This is an experience of relaxation, with coffee and food.  I felt like I could sit and enjoy comfortable conversion all morning long.
As a plus, their coffee and pancakes make a wonderful addition to the experience!

Looking for a great coffee shop that's more than just a place to grab a latte? Look no further than this hidden gem in town! Not only does it serve incredible drinks and tasty food, but it also provides an opportunity for folks to get their life back on track and learn work skills.

The Honey bee latte is a must-try, but the real magic is in the community. By supporting this coffee shop, you're helping to restore hope and give people a chance to be a part of life once again. Plus, with an event space that can comfortably fit up to thirty people, it's a great spot for meetings or seminars.

William, the manager, is incredibly knowledgeable and helpful when it comes to managing the event space. So, whether you're looking for a spot to catch up with friends or host a professional gathering, this coffee shop has got you covered. Come for the coffee, stay for the community and see how hope is being restored here!
This place is so wonderful and is such a great cause that I can’t put words together to properly review. Just go!

Great idea for a restaurant that should be fully supported by the community, with decent food and nice atmosphere, but with slow service during busy lunch times (that can be excused as most of the staff are from the rescue mission). I had the New Orleans chicken sandwich with a side of home fries. The sandwich was huge, but was not sauced as expected, since the order was mixed up and they had put the sauce on the side. The staff is being trained so we know going in that service may be slow. Other orders like the French toast were delicious. I will be back to support this restaurant with their hopeful message.
Everyone was extremely pleasant and the food and service was great, I had the Cajun skillet, which I recommend, even the toast was delicious 😎

Awesome breakfast! The place is a little loud when it gets busy and service a little slow but we were in no rush and really enjoyed eating here.

They're doing great work here. The food is wonderful and the drinks are very large mugs of good coffee. We've attended here several times for work outing lunches, and are 100% behind the mission. Thank y'all for the work you do!
Great food, service and cause. Try the breakfast sandwich, grits and ginger tea!

The French toast was very appetizing. As for the service, I was not satisfied. We booked a private party and they barley checked on us and the food took forever to come out. One of the servers was passive aggressive when asked to bring an item with the reply of "I only have 2 hands".
Great service , short but very good menu. Well executed food.
Really good stop if you are in town. Very good portions and good food. A coffee shop area for relaxing.

The food and drinks were high quality, flavorful, and definitely made with love! Their menu changes so that it’s always seasonal and fresh. Very affordable for such high-end dishes. Amazing environment, a great mission, and excellent service

Beautiful neighborhood cafe with a purpose❤️. The employees are warm and the place is so welcoming...I love the decor....there are lots of tables and chairs to sit and work and plenty of parking spots. I have tried their chai lattes and their muffins and they are amazing and served warm in the mornings. It is a very popular spot and it's nice to see it busy even at 7:30am. Definitely try it out.
Food and coffee are great, so are the people! Highly recommend stopping here if in the Charlotte area on a weekday

Atmosphere is incredible. The place is kept clean and the coffee was good too. My only complaint is the staff were impolite. Had an awkward interaction with a man standing at the host stand when I came inside.  He didn’t greet me when I came in or say anything to me at all so I simply said  “hi how are you” and he answered back kind of rudely “what”? It was weird. Also when I ordered my coffee I asked nicely if I could please have a mug instead of the plastic coffee cup and this girl grabbed it for me with an attitude

This place has great coffee honestly. You can find comparable quality meals at other similarly styled places for cheaper or same price but their coffee quality keeps me coming back to pay the extra dollar. Very friendly service also which goes a long way at a relaxing place like this.
I'd give 6 stars if I could! The service is SPECTACULAR! The food was yummy and not badly priced. I loved the ambiance of the entire atmosphere. I'll definitely be back soon!

Love this place! Went for the first time today and not only was the staff great but the food was delicious!! All of our meals were so good and the coffee was as well. Our waiters and the rest of the staff were so kind, one man even brought a bowl of blueberries for my 1 year old :). Can’t wait to go back!
Loved the music and the mission of Community Matters. I needed a place to work for a few hours and the customer service was outstanding! What a blessing!!
Firstly, I love what this place does for the community.  Secondly, the food, the service, and the atmosphere are all perfect.  I highly recommend coming here if you're in the area.

This place is amazing in so many ways! The breakfast was great and super delicious in a very nice and inviting atmosphere. But what tops it all is the cause and mission of this place! Keep up the great work!!
This has always been one of my favorite places to get coffee in charlotte. Not only are they helping the community but they are incredibly friendly and have great coffee and food.
Amazing French toast
Had an amazing BLT. Service was good and great spot also to do some work during lunch. I try lots of BLT’s in the area and this one really blew me away.
First time visiting and the food was amazing
One of my favorite spots in Charlotte! A must for coffee and breakfast/brunch.
Great food and customer service!

Great atmosphere, nice aesthetics and impressive mission statement with attentive service and tasty food. If you are looking for not just great food but a warm experience too then you must visit this place!
It is good - portions are substantial and well made. Service is very attentive.
The food, the staff, the coffee, the atmosphere... everything was amazing! So happy we found this gem.

reviews_data.review_text: Great service, delicious food, and clean space. I will be back.
Simple food, great atmosphere and an awesome mission. Would gladly come back! Overall a great experience, had the egg sandwich and it was tasty.

We had senico and he was absolutely incredible. He had patience for everyone including tables with lesser mannerisms. He was kind and made sure we were happy and satisfied and even cracked a few jokes with us here and there. Best service I have honestly ever received when being in charlotte!!!! Thank you senico!!!
Great dining experience and group meeting space!

Me and two of my friends decided to check out a new restaurant in Charlotte, NC. When we arrived at the restaurant we were greeted with a big smile and we loved the ambience of Community Matters Cafe. The menu was concise and simple with both Breakfast, Brunch, and Lunch options.

I ordered the hot Cinnamon Bun Mocha and it was delicious! The cream on top was so good and it felt like I was having a dessert beverage. For Lunch I ordered the New Orleans Fried Chicken Sandwich with cheddar grits. I loved the cheesy grits and it was yummy. The chicken sandwich wasn’t too spicy and it was straight fire!

Overall, it was delicious and I totally recommend this restaurant if you are in the Uptown area of Charlotte, NC!

Was so excited to try this place afte le hearing great things. Service was not good at all. Waited 45 mins for our food. Server didn’t come by during that time at all. When food came order was incorrect. Then I had to wait longer for it to be re done. I’m giving one star because the coffee was really good. But I likely will not return.
Very good food & coffee!
Always enjoy the Cafel they never disappoint!

reviews_data.review_text:
Great food, amazing staff, large and comfortable space. I loved the prosperi-Tea . It’s their take on a medicine ball but it’s so much better. Great cafe to come and hang out or have a small meeting.
Large (free) parking lot.

Can’t wait to come back when it’s a little warmer and take advantage of the outdoor patio seating.
Amazing place!! Great food, great service and wonderful cause!! Family friendly and the patio is great for small pets!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you!

reviews_data.review_text: My friend and I dined at the Cafe today and our food and coffee was excellent.  The service was kind of absent, though.  We had not received our bill which is primarily the reason we were still at our table.  The FOH manager came to our table and said we needed to leave our table because of people having reservations.  We explained that we have not received our bill.  He said "no problem, I'll take care of you".  However, he never took care of us.  We were a little taken aback by the situation because he simply disappeared.  I went to the barista counter and explained the situation and she apologized profusely.  She was a wonderful person and even gave us a free coffee because we had explained we wanted to take a latte to go.  That was completely unexpected, but much appreciated after we felt like we were being kicked out.  I would have liked to speak to the FOH manager again, but he never did end up coming back to speak/assist us.
Over priced
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Billy, so sorry you think so.  We are however in Uptown, (with FREE parking by the way), and the cost of food has gone up over 40% in the last year.  The average lunch in Uptown is $15 so we feel we are right in line with other full-service restaurants.  We’d love a chance to win your business back.  
Show this review and response to Will or Paula and we will gladly offer you a 20% discount on your whole meal when you return.  Be sure to tell them as you arrive.

reviews_data.review_text: The best chai latte I’ve ever had in my life and I’ve had alot! Also had the breakfast bowl substituted with turkey sausage and it was amazing. New favorite spot.
reviews_data.owner_answer: George, so glad you found us !

reviews_data.review_text: The atmosphere, food, coffee and perhaps most significantly their mission make this place my favorite in Charlotte.

Came here for a coffee meeting recently and was pleasantly surprised. The space is pretty big and it was bustling with people on a Wednesday morning having meetings or getting some work done. The energy was great!

I didn’t eat breakfast but I enjoyed a really good gingerbread latte.

Located near uptown and lots of free parking in their parking lot.

reviews_data.review_text: Really great atmosphere, delicious drinks, and a wonderful purpose! We were visiting from out of town and wanted a good coffee shop to hang out at for a morning. I could have spent many hours here!
reviews_data.owner_answer: So glad you found us

reviews_data.review_text: These guys are on point. Great location, they support a legit mission. Eating in or taking out the coffee and food is good. I recommend.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Scooter, we appreciate the love.

reviews_data.review_text: This is a great place all around. I would probably return to this spot if I ever came around here again!

We also got some pastries. We enjoyed the miso blondie, lemon cheesecake cookie sammie, and the molasses cookie sammie. The molasses cookie sammie was my favorite.

reviews_data.review_text:
Wow! I did not have a good experience at this place. I am a remote worker, wanted to get some coffee and breakfast while checking some emails before taking some meetings at home later, and this place was highly recommended. As soon as we walked in, the environment was already a bit unwelcoming and the barista taking our order was short with us. Once we got the coffee we ordered, the extra hot drink didn't have a sleeve on it so we had to ask for one because it was too hot to hold.
We decided (against our better judgement) to go ahead with our plan to order food so we were seated, and sat for a long while before being able to put an order in — seems like the waitress may have forgotten we were there or not have noticed. My partner had just travelled a couple hours really early in the morning and so went to the bathroom to change their shoes and pants, and a waitress followed them and checked on them, maybe thinking they were doing something suspicious?
Once the food came, we were surprised to see the focaccia de jour had pork on it, and unfortunately my partner doesn't eat pork (our bad, we should have asked, but we also weren't told anything about what it came with, and the menu only said olive oil — which it didn't seem to have either). We waited ages for a server to come to our table so we could ask for something to replace it, like regular toast, and then another few ages for that to get to us. At the point that it did, it was nearing the time I needed to leave, and my partner was feeling extremely uncomfortable and anxious and so I went ahead to the host's stand to ask for to go boxes and to go ahead and close the check — it probably would have taken another 20 minutes to wait for someone to come to our table again.
If you're visibly queer or dress alternatively, I don't recommend coming here. I don't usually have any issues with either of these things in Charlotte, but the entire time we felt so incredibly judged and got constant stares from not only all of the staff but also the other customers. Service was not great, slow, and not very attentive. Did not come to check on us except to give us the check. I do appreciate that they removed the focaccia from our bill since my partner was not able to eat it. My partner did enjoy the french toast I ordered, but I was overall disappointed by the food and did not really like it much. The one positive interaction I had was with the host, who was very attentive, helped me get the boxes, and greeted me with a kind smile and was polite. Everyone else in the entire cafe made us feel very uncomfortable and unwelcome.
I do think the mission of the cafe is lovely and it seems like they have provided some great experiences for many customers, but unfortunately our visit was disappointing.
This place is absolutely amazing. The staff and the guests are so welcoming and friendly.
Pretty big breakfast spot. Wasn’t super busy at 7am. Friendly staff. Simple but yummy food. Decent coffee. Big parking lot. Community focused.

reviews_data.review_text: Waited too long for our drinks. I understand it can be busy but over 5 minutes and plenty off staff is a bit much for two simple espresso drinks. On top of that the cappuccino had a weird aftertaste like skim milk.

This was my first time, I was excited about the concept of a co working restaurant space. I ordered a beverage from their menu, and asked about an ingredient on a menu item for breakfast. Out of the two people taking orders, and the manager and other workers behind the counter, no one knew what about the menu item, so I passed on the food. After I ordered the drink, A 5th person ended up knowing about the menu and informed me of what it was.

So I ordered a beverage, with one modification. I waited at the counter for about five minutes For my drink (no line) And then was asked what I was waiting for. I let them know my drink order had not yet arrived so I was still waiting on that. They had lost the drink ticket, which is fine, completely understand. I let them know what I would like again and wait a couple more minutes. Then another someone to come up and tell me they cannot make the drink on ice (as I had ordered it) because they don’t have the capability to make the iced drink that I ordered. Mind you, they offer iced and frozen beverages.

After about 20 minutes, I get my drink and they did not include the modification (adding a syrup). I go back up to the coffee bar and ask to confirm that they put vanilla and lavender in the beverage as I had ordered, and was told nope only the lavender was in there. I stood there Foolishly, expecting them to offer to at least put the correct syrup in the drink, since I was informed 10 minutes after I ordered it, but they could not make the drink that I ordered. No offer to try and make anything right. I packed up my stuff and left, I will not be coming back.

I can look past not knowing your menu, I can look past losing my order, I can look past you telling me you can’t make the drink that I already paid for 10 minutes after I have been waiting, but after all that and it’s not even the flavor I ordered? Very disappointed.
